==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stonecrop
<hw>Stone"crop`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>st⟦amac⟧ncropp</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A sort of tree.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Mortimer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Any low succulent plant of the
genus <gen>Sedum</gen>, esp. <spn>Sedum acre</spn>, which is common on
bare rocks in Europe, and is spreading in parts of America. See
<er>Orpine</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Virginian stonecrop</b></col>, <it>or</it>
<col><b>Ditch stonecrop</b></col></mcol>, <cd>an American plant
(<spn>Penthorum sedoides</spn>).</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stonecutter</ent>⟦br⟧
